## `portdial()` contract

```c
/* plan9port: delegates to httpdial(sockpath) — proxy must be running */
/* 9front:    dial("tcp!host!port") + tlsClient() — direct TLS, sockpath ignored */
HTTPConn *portdial(char *host, char *port, char *sockpath);
```

All callers pass the real API hostname and "443".  On plan9port the proxy
already speaks to that host; on 9front we dial it directly.

