## `9ai-acme-native.c` architecture

Three procs:
- `outproc`   — reads `/mnt/9ai/output`; streams text into window body
- `aiproc`    — reads `/mnt/9ai/event`; renders thinking/tool/status lines
- `eventproc` — reads `/mnt/acme/<id>/event`; dispatches Send/Stop/Steer/New/Clear/Models/Sessions

All window writes serialised with `winlk`.  `winappend()` uses `addr="$"` +
`data` write to always append at the end regardless of cursor position.

Tag commands:
- **Send** — writes last paragraph (or dot selection) to `/mnt/9ai/message`
- **Stop** — writes `abort\n` to `/mnt/9ai/ctl`
- **Steer** — writes last paragraph to `/mnt/9ai/steer`
- **New** — writes `new` to `/mnt/9ai/session/new`
- **Clear** — writes `clear\n` to `/mnt/9ai/ctl`; erases body lines 2..$
- **Models** — opens `+models` window from `/mnt/9ai/models`; middle-click a model id to switch
- **Sessions** — opens `+sessions` window from `~/lib/9ai/sessions/`; middle-click a UUID to load

