## Known 9front runtime considerations

- **TLS cert verification** — `tlsClient()` with `serverName` set performs SNI.
  Copilot endpoints have valid certs; should work out of the box.
- **`threadwaitchan` race** — if `nbrecvp(threadwaitchan())` races with
  internal thread cleanup, switch `portwaitnohang()` to use a dedicated watcher
  proc that forward-sends to a private channel.
- **`/mnt/acme` vs `$acmepath`** — some 9front setups mount acme elsewhere.
  If needed, add `-A acmedir` flag to `9ai-acme`.
- **`/mnt/9ai` mountpoint** — `9ai` must be started with `-m /mnt/9ai` before
  running `9ai-acme`.
